@ summary: phlo_serve worker-mode soak fixture. mirror() echoes its args (correct dispatch under
@          load); probe() calls a resource object twice so the test can assert both within-request
@          object identity ('fresh' then 'visited') and that phlo('tech/reset') gives each request a
@          clean object again ('fresh') - the state isolation the worker loop must keep between
@          requests, on ZTS as well as NTS.

static mirror(...$args) => $args

static probe => [%box->visit(), %box->visit()]
